)` via `kotlin.KotlinVersion.CURRENT`\n  - `callStaticMethod(...)` via `scala.util.Properties.versionNumberString()`\n- Asserted that the runtime metadata header includes detected `kt` and `sc` major/minor entries.\n- Made the existing top-level `Elasticsearch_javaTest` class `public` to satisfy test-class visibility rules.\n\nFiles changed:\n- `tests/src/co.elastic.clients/elasticsearch-java/9.0.3/build.gradle`\n- `tests/src/co.elastic.clients/elasticsearch-java/9.0.3/src/test/java/co_elastic_clients/elasticsearch_java/Elasticsearch_javaTest.java`\n- `tests/src/co.elastic.clients/elasticsearch-java/9.0.3/src/test/java/co_elastic_clients/elasticsearch_java/LanguageRuntimeVersionsTest.java`\n\nTests were not run, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_096af9234d5bb14c016a40e82d28908197881d29a865bdd65b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2824, "output": 1697, "cacheRead": 45056, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49577, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782638616088, "responseId": "resp_096af9234d5bb14c016a40e81939d48197a7caed89b22849bc"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating behavior differences**\n\nI'm considering that just asserting presence might pass both tests, but I haven't checked the behavior differences. When I say \"same behavior,\" I mean the test assertions are the same, not that I'm observing every detail. If I'm under JVM with specific circumstances and it shows green but behaves differently, could it be considered hidden? It's not catching the missing resource metadata, so I'm wondering if the dynamic access target is actually reflection, and if that’s acceptable.\n\n**Considering resource handling**\n\nIf a resource is missing but a method invoked returns empty, that indicates missing resource metadata, not reflection. I'm wondering if the agent should include the resource. It might be better to make it robust by adding metadata, although that could be forbidden. But if the native method fails due to a missing resource, how do I handle it? Should I use Kotlin for the field and the `System` method? It seems tricky with hardcoded class names in language runtimes.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_096af9234d5bb14c016a40e819e13c819797358226571c0aa3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQOgtiooqigHBhok4KEpwFt1Z-Snd_r1clP02mm7SZZE5dqHIJ8xKxhowxkdYOGr2-wa2g9hsSfs7arE9o4DqWDM8FWgadwDwISSNKELDVsf90QXYeU3DQ8VCeqiLoRUk5av-WSS91pXv3uuDavhOppNX5ZhzpeC_PZsGpUUvoKZAi_GFK3_SoyKjR2aVputn0VNq8jXgZ5znvH732unYoIRyB-wDHz1V7BfzWWJ74za8AbG4YPVhdQCGjGNYnMreYgmxt5uflScVzlNLBryuxOwocbU13P9aickuCcPdFCma1f05TMczqJv15YDqCpFbkVN2mLhMz7s9p9i7R5zQr6k1CtBrBEKmDdDs_twdzOGMn6hJlS_QG9YcU-Jkj1-n-Lto8miu2tQlnQqxQahlmsdmy3ARqrY80GFgprjoUaP3D-tFs7rqJMWvhAeiIgGScxWa_QNoB-xMPNNHg_aUOlDfMPf8bmzWH83QDcR5gPVNBk6EtLllsl_k_U9Ef9yYKzEdvKPdsMSvYx9ehVDlqKdj-LtUjkKtWid4_f900dNA7AKGuJzxUbo6XsgcRecItkyur6bz-nEyr5a0r8N2wNCBISQrZXnPD7hFTvu2DJ01ryDLOVB2I_lnaisuuZDcIptTmcWOQusGVMrwho8XYHQ3BGp5Xs1AzXrH41led62iAtYPhUVNcDc7w